aS' This, monks, is the fourth future danger, un-arisen at present that will arise in the future. Be alert to it and, being alert, work to get rid of it. Furthermore, in the course of the future there will be monks who will live in close association with monastery attendants and novices. As they interact with monastery attendants and novices, they can be expected to live intent on storing up all kinds of possessions and to stake out crops and fields. This is the fifth future danger... This, monks, is the fifth future danger, un-arisen at present that will arise in the future. Be alert to it and, being alert, work to get rid of it.'
