aS" On one occasion Ven. Ananda was staying near Savatthi in Jeta's Grove, Anathapindika's monastery. Then early in the morning he put on his robes and, carrying his bowl and outer robe, went into Savatthi for alms with Ven. Vangisa as his attendant monk. Now at that time dissatisfaction with the chaste life had arisen in Ven. Vangisa. Lust invaded his mind. So he addressed Ven. Ananda with this verse: "
p616
aS" With sensual lust I burn.\xe2\x80\xa8My mind is on fire.\xe2\x80\xa8Please, Gotama, from compassion,\xe2\x80\xa8tell me how to put it out.  From distorted perception\xe2\x80\xa8\xc2\xa0your mind is on fire.\xe2\x80\xa8Shun the theme of the beautiful\xe2\x80\xa8\xc2\xa0accompanied by lust.\xe2\x80\xa8See mental fabrications as other,\xe2\x80\xa8\xc2\xa0as stress,\xe2\x80\xa8\xc2\xa0and not-self. Extinguish your great lust.\xe2\x80\xa8\xc2\xa0Don't keep burning again and again.\xe2\x80\xa8 Develop the mind\xe2\x80\xa8 -- well centered and one --\xe2\x80\xa8\xc2\xa0in the foul,\xe2\x80\xa8through the foul.\xe2\x80\xa8Have your mindfulness\xe2\x80\xa8\xc2\xa0immersed in the body.\xe2\x80\xa8Be one who pursues\xe2\x80\xa8\xc2\xa0disenchantment.\xe2\x80\xa8Develop the theme-less.\xe2\x80\xa8Cast out conceit.\xe2\x80\xa8Then, from breaking through\xe2\x80\xa8\xc2\xa0conceit,\xe2\x80\xa8\xc2\xa0you will go on your way at peace. "
